title: How has compliance with good practice changed?
analysis_commentary: Data are only available for all nine indicators from 2006 onwards. All indicators have generally been improving over time. The only exception to this is 'patients having a brain scan within 24 hours', which dipped to a low of 42.0% in 2006. The highest performing indicator in most years is 'rehabilitation goals agreed', which has the highest compliance rate of 94.0% in 2010.
data_source: Royal College of Physicians, National Stroke Audit
